The paper discusses the implementation of an accelerator for memory-augmented neural networks (MANNs) on a field-programmable gate array (FPGA), which falls under the category of hardware design and implementation (cs.ET). The focus of the paper is on energy efficiency, which suggests a potential overlap with the sub-category of energy-efficient computing (cs.EM). MANNs are designed for question-answering tasks, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper presents measurements on the bAbI dataset, which is a popular benchmark for evaluating MANNs, indicating a potential overlap with the sub-category of natural language processing (cs.NE).
